        <div class="svc-pillar-content">
          <span class="section-eyebrow">— 02 · Trusts and foundations</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">
            Trust and <em>foundation</em><br />structures done seriously.
          </h2>
          <p>Trusts segregate assets, distribute economic benefit and survive death. Foundations — where used internationally — offer similar effects with different governance characteristics. Used together, they create a layered architecture that no single vehicle can replicate.</p>
          <ul class="svc-pillar-list">
            <li>Discretionary family trust with carefully drafted appointor and trustee lines.</li>
            <li>Unit trust beneath the family trust for asset segregation and partner economics.</li>
            <li>Charitable trust or ancillary fund for the family's philanthropy and tax positioning.</li>
            <li>Offshore foundation or PTC structures where the international footprint warrants it.</li>
            <li>Deed-of-variation and successor-appointor provisions tested across multiple lifetimes.</li>
          </ul>

